name: The Sympathizer
overview: An espionage thriller and cross-culture satire about the struggles of a half-French, half-Vietnamese communist spy during the final days of the Vietnam War and his resulting exile in the United States.

episodes.name: Death Wish
episodes.overview: With the fall of Saigon imminent, the Captain juggles the communist party, the South Vietnamese army, his CIA handler and his conscience.

episodes.name: Good Little Asian
episodes.overview: As he adjusts to life in Los Angeles, the Captain is forced to find someone to implicate when the General begins to suspect a mole.

episodes.name: Love It or Leave It
episodes.overview: The Captain and Bon craft a plan to quell the General's anxieties. Later, the Captain meets the Auteur, who wants to make a film about war.

episodes.name: Give Us Some Good Lines
episodes.overview: As a reluctant consultant on a Hollywood film, the Captain navigates the egos and personalities of an increasingly chaotic production.

episodes.name: All for One
episodes.overview: After a lengthy stint at the hospital, the Captain discovers that the General has started recruiting for a secret military operation.

episodes.name: The Oriental Mode of Destruction
episodes.overview: Convinced that the General's military operation is doomed, the Captain searches for ways to expose the mission and save Bon.

episodes.name: Endings Are Hard, Aren't They?
episodes.overview: Back in Vietnam, the Captain is forced to tell his story… and confront the decisions that haunt his past.
